Herein consists our distinguishing excellence, that in the hour of emergency
we show the greatest courage, and yet debate beforehand the expediency of
our measures. The courage of others is the result of ignorance; deliberation
makes them cowards. And those undoubtedly must be owned to have the greatest
souls, who, most acutely sensible of the miseries of war and the sweets
of peace, are not hence in the least deterred from facing danger.
